<headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 31 at 7:42PM EDT  by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...Snow showers to impact areas in northwestern Indiana and far
southwestern Lower Michigan this evening...
An area of snow showers will rapidly drop southeast across much of
far southwestern Lower Michigan and northern Indiana through 9 PM
EDT. Motorists may encounter brief visibility drops to a mile or
less with localized drops to 1/4 mile possible. The snow may
accumulate on roads and bridges in the heavier snow showers as
temperatures fall below freezing. Local accumulations of up to an
inch of snow are possible.
Use caution if encountering one of these snow showers when
travelling this evening.</description>
